# Library / candidate / reference capture — auto-merge

Anton has **standing permission** to auto-merge without separate manual approval when **all** conditions below hold.

## Allowed auto-merge class

`LIBRARY-CAPTURE / CANDIDATE-CAPTURE / REFERENCE-ONLY / DESTINATION-SHAPE`

## Allowed content (docs capture only)

- Product candidates, tool references, article references
- Roadmap / destination-shape notes, evaluation candidates, benchmark products
- Marketing automation candidates, future chat/concierge references
- AI / video / article generation candidate notes
- Operator-supplied rationale for why a tool is worth tracking

## Allowed paths (unless repo convention says otherwise)

- `docs/product/**`, `docs/strategy/**`, `docs/research/**`, `docs/tools/**`
- `artifacts/chat_history.md`
- Lightweight index in `docs/CORPFLOW_SHARED_TODO.md` **only if** a relevant future-candidates/library section already exists
- `docs/decisions/JOURNAL.md` **only if** repo convention requires a JE row

## Auto-merge requirements

- Docs-only PR; `git diff --name-only` limited to approved paths above (plus this rule file when updating policy)
- No app/runtime code, `.env*`, new env var names, secrets, tokens, credentials, private URLs, chat IDs, passwords, API keys, or Infisical paths
- No n8n workflow changes; no L3/server commands
- No containers, Docker Compose, GitHub Actions, scripts, cron, systemd, migrations, Prisma, API routes, middleware, package files, or Vercel config
- PR body or captured doc must state **`NO IMPLEMENTATION AUTHORIZED`**
- Status wording must be `REFERENCE-ONLY`, `CANDIDATE-CAPTURED`, `SERIOUS-CANDIDATE / EVALUATE-FIRST`, or `DESTINATION-SHAPE` — **not** `AUTHORIZED`, `SELECTED`, `IMPLEMENTING`, or `COMPLETE`
- Preserve standing holds: no restic (unless separately authorized), no new self-hosted tools, no Chatwoot/Open WebUI/Dify/Coolify/Langfuse/AgentSpan/OpenJarvis/generic chatbot frameworks, no n8n migration, no public port exposure, no additional containers

## Pre-merge verification

1. `git diff --stat` is docs-only
2. `git diff --name-only` ⊆ approved paths
3. Scan for obvious secret-like strings
4. CI green if it runs; if docs-only and CI skipped by convention, record why no runtime verification was needed

## Do not auto-merge if

- Any app/runtime, env, infrastructure, monitoring, backup, n8n, deployment, auth, database, or production-behavior change
- Implementation wording or tool authorization ambiguity
- CI fails or merge conflicts exist
- PR is not clearly docs-only

If blocked, **stop and ask Anton**.

## Post-merge response format

Report: **Status** / **What I checked** / **What changed** / **Merge SHA** / **Current state** / **Confirmation that no implementation was authorized**
